     <profileDesc>
        <abstract><p>Order of <persName ref="#mirIbrahim">Mir Ibrahim</persName>, an employee of Prince <persName ref="#muradBakhsh">Murad Bakhsh</persName>, to the headmen (muqaddam), landlords (chaudhri), record-keepers (qanungo) and residents of the district (pargana) <placeName ref="#pgDhar">Dhar</placeName>, notifying them that the peasants of the village <placeName ref="#tornod">Tornod</placeName> may not attempt to use water from the tank that adjoins the villages <placeName ref="#naugaon">Naugaon</placeName> 
           and <placeName ref="#khilchipur">Qilchipur [Khilchipur]</placeName> because the residents of those villages have owned these water rights since antiquity.</p></abstract>       
